title: Spotify's Top 10 most streamed tracks
text:
The Canadian Press - ONLINE EDITION Spotify's Top 10 most streamed tracks By: The Associated Press Report Error 
The following list represents the most streamed tracks on Spotify, based on the number of people who shared it divided by the number who listened to it, from Friday, Oct. 9 to Thursday, Oct. 15 via Facebook, Tumblr, Twitter and Spotify. 
CANADA 
1. Drake, "Hotline Bling" (Cash Money Records Inc.) 
2. Justin Bieber, "What Do You Mean?" (Def Jam Recordings) 
3. The Weeknd, "The Hills" (Republic Records) 
4. The Weeknd, "Can't Feel My Face" (Republic Records) 
5. Major Lazer & DJ Snake featuring MO, "Lean On" (Mad Decent) 
6. R. City featuring Adam Levine, "Locked Away" (Kemosabe Records) 
7. Selena Gomez, "Good for You" (Interscope Records) 
8. Drake and Future, "Jumpman" (Cash Money Records Inc.) 
9. Ellie Goulding, "On My Mind" (Polydor Ltd.) 
& Disciples, "How Deep is Your Love" (Sony Music Entertainment UK Ltd.) 
& Ryan Lewis featuring Eric Nally, Melle Mel, Kool Moe Dee & Grandmaster Caz, "Downtown" (Macklemore, LLC) 
& DJ Snake featuring MO, "Lean On" (Mad Decent) 
& Disciples, "How Deep is Your Love" (Sony Music Entertainment UK Ltd.)
